-- Gui custom functions:

local loadImage = nil
local function randString(len)
	local chars = {}
	for i = 1, len or math.random(16, 32) do
		chars[i] = string.char(math.random(33, 230))
	end
	return table.concat(chars)
end

rconsole = {
	print = function(text)
		if rconsoleprint then
			rconsoleprint(text)
			return true
		end

		if isStudio then
			print(text)
		end

		return false
	end,

	info = function(text)
		if rconsoleinfo then
			rconsoleinfo(text)
			return true
		end

		if isStudio then
			print(text)
		end

		return false
	end,

	warn = function(text)
		if rconsolewarn then
			rconsolewarn(text)
			return true
		end

		if isStudio then
			warn(text)
		end

		return false
	end,

	error = function(text)
		if rconsoleerr then
			rconsoleerr(text)
			return true
		end

		if isStudio then
			error(text)
		end

		return false
	end,

	clear = function()
		if rconsoleclear then
			rconsoleclear()
			return true
		end

		return false
	end,
}

	rconsole.warn("Fake getenv called!")
	return fakeenv

local clonefunction = function(funct: funct)
	if not funct then
		return nil
	end

	if clonefunction then
		return clonefunction(funct)
	end

	return function(...)
		return typeof(funct) == "function" and funct(...) or funct
	end
end

local newcclosure = newcclosure or function(...)
	rconsole.warn("Fake newcclosure called!")
	return ...
end

local hookfunction = hookfunction or function(...)
	rconsole.warn("Fake hookfunction called!")
	return ...
end

local hookmetamethod = hookmetamethod or function(...)
	rconsole.warn("Fake hookmetamethod called!")
	return ...
end

local cloneref = cloneref or function(...)
	rconsole.warn("Fake cloneref called!")
	return ...
end

local getgc = getgc or function(...)
	rconsole.warn("Fake getgc called!")
	return {}
end

local setreadonly = setreadonly or function(...)
	rconsole.warn("Fake setreadonly called!")
	return ...
end

local sethiddenproperty = sethiddenproperty or function(...)
	rconsole.warn("Fake newcclosure called!")
	return ...
end

local getnamecallmethod = getnamecallmethod or function(...)
	rconsole.warn("Fake getnamecallmethod called!")
	return ""
end

	return false 
end

-- [[ TEMPORARY SHIT !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! ]]
if isiosdevice() then
	local oldnmc
	local contentProvider = game:GetService("ContentProvider")

	for k,v in pairs(getgc(true)) do
		if pcall(function() return rawget(v,"indexInstance") end) and type(rawget(v,"indexInstance")) == "table" and (rawget(v,"indexInstance"))[1] == "kick" then
			v.tvk = {"kick", function()
				return game.Workspace:WaitForChild("")
			end}
		end
	end

	oldnmc = hookmetamethod(game, "__namecall", function(self, ...)
		local args = {...}
		local method = getnamecallmethod()

		if self == contentProvider and (method == "PreloadAsync" or method == "preloadAsync") and table.find(args[1], game.CoreGui) then
			return {}
		end

		return oldnmc(self, ...)
	end)

	local oldf
	oldf = hookfunction(contentProvider.PreloadAsync, function(self, ...)
		local args = {...}

		if table.find(args[1], game.CoreGui) then
			return {}
		end

		return oldf(self, ...)
	end)

	local placeId = game.PlaceId
	local games = {
		emergency = {
			[2534724415] = true,
			[6417675492] = true,
			[11845704379] = true,
			[15885203328] = true
		}
	}

	if games.emergency[placeId] then
		local playerService = cloneref(game:GetService("Players"));
		local localPlayer = playerService.LocalPlayer;

		local set_thread_identity = (typeof(syn) == "table" and syn.set_thread_identity) or (setidentity or setthreadcontext);
		local hookfunc = (replaceclosure or hookfunction);

		local last_script_hash = "60f741d6331abb59d37583fea790c929735a119c77f7e25216942e906079e766a217a57670a6d1fb9a12899b4b9245f1";

		local function bypassFunc()
			repeat
				wait();
			until (localPlayer.Character and localPlayer.Character:FindFirstChild("Interaction Handler"));

			set_thread_identity(2);

			local getTextFunc = rawget(rawget(require(localPlayer.Character["Interaction Handler"].InteractionActions), "Locker"), "GetText");

			set_thread_identity(7);

			if (typeof(syn) == "table" or executescript) then
				if (getscripthash(localPlayer.Character["Interaction Handler"].InteractionActions) ~= last_script_hash) then
					if (not isfile("warning.data")) then
						writefile("warning.data", "");
						return localPlayer:Kick("the anticheat appears to have updated, please re-execute if you want to use it anyway.\n\nThe bypass might be patched.");    
					end;
				end;
			end

			if (not getTextFunc) then
				for i, v in next, getgc() do
					if (typeof(v) ~= "function") then continue end;

					if (getinfo(v).name == "GetText") then
						getTextFunc = v;
						break;
					end;
				end;

				if (not getTextFunc) then
					return localPlayer:Kick("failed to find required functions - this normally means the game has updated.");
				end;
			end;

			local tfunc;
			for i, v in next, getupvalues(getTextFunc) do
				if (typeof(v) ~= "function") then continue end;

				if (getinfo(v).name == "O") then
					tfunc = v;
					break;
				end;
			end;

			if (not tfunc) then
				tfunc = getupvalue(getTextFunc, 15);
				if (typeof(tfunc) ~= "function" or #getinfo(tfunc).name ~= 1) then
					return localPlayer:Kick("failed to find required functions (2) - this normally means the game has updated.")
				end
			end;

			local old_q;old_q = hookfunc(tfunc, function(...) 
				local ret = old_q(...);
				if (typeof(ret) == "function" and islclosure(ret)) then
					local old;old = hookfunc(ret, function(...)
						local nfunc = debug.info(2, "f");
						if (not nfunc or debug.info(nfunc, "s") == "[C]") then
							return wait(9e9);    
						end;
						local cfunc = debug.getinfo(nfunc).name;
						if (not cfunc or cfunc == "") then
							return old(...);    
						end;
						if (cfunc == "pcall") then
							return wait(9e9);
						end;
						return old(...);
					end)
				end;
				return ret;
			end);
		end;

		bypassFunc();
		localPlayer.CharacterAdded:Connect(bypassFunc)
	end
end

	end

--[[
		[ TOAST ]
]]

do
	--local lastIndex = 999999
	--local lastToasts = {}

	local show = function(text: string, isLong: boolean, title: string)
		if tonumber(isLong) then
			local num = tonumber(isLong)
			isLong = num == 1 and true or false
		end

		isLong = isLong and true or false

		--

		local newToast = Main.Toast:Clone()
		misc.protectInstances(newToast)
		--newToast.Name = randString()

		newToast:FindFirstChildWhichIsA("TextLabel"):Destroy()
		newToast:FindFirstChildWhichIsA("TextLabel"):Destroy()

		local description = Main.ToastDescription:Clone()
		misc.protectInstances(description)
		--description.Name = randString()
		description.Text = text

		if title then
			local label = Main.ToastTitle:Clone()
			misc.protectInstances(label)
			--label.Name = randString()
			label.Text = title
			label.Parent = newToast
		else
			description.Size = UDim2.fromScale(1, 0.9)
		end

		description.Parent = newToast
		if not getgenv().arceus.garbage.toastIndex then
			getgenv().arceus.garbage.toastIndex = 999999
		end

		if not getgenv().arceus.garbage.toasts then
			getgenv().arceus.garbage.toasts = {}
		end

		newToast.ZIndex = getgenv().arceus.garbage.toastIndex
		getgenv().arceus.garbage.toastIndex -= 1

		local toastContainer = newToast:FindFirstChildWhichIsA("Frame")
		local toastBar = toastContainer:FindFirstChildWhichIsA("Frame")
		toastBar.Size = UDim2.fromScale(0, 1)

		local ogSize = Main.Toast.Size
		local finalPosition = UDim2.fromScale(0.7, 0.725)
		local ogPosition = UDim2.fromScale(0.7 + ogSize.X.Scale * 1.25, 0.725)

		newToast.Position = ogPosition
		newToast.Parent = Main.Main
		newToast.Visible = true

		getgenv().arceus.garbage.toasts[newToast] = newToast.ZIndex
		pages.handleCustomDrag(newToast)

		local offset = UDim2.fromScale(0, ogSize.Y.Scale * 1.25)
		for v, _ in pairs(getgenv().arceus.garbage.toasts) do
			local pos = nil

			if v.Position == finalPosition then
				pos = finalPosition - offset

			elseif v.Position == finalPosition - offset then
				pos = finalPosition - offset - offset

			elseif v.Position == finalPosition - offset - offset then
				pos = finalPosition - offset - offset - offset

			end

			if pos then
				TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(v, TweenInfo.new(
					0.5, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.In, 0, false, 0
					), { Position = pos }):Play()
			end
		end

		--

		TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(newToast, TweenInfo.new(
			0.5, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.In, 0, false, 0
			), { Position = finalPosition }):Play()

		local running = true
		local duration = isLong and 5 or 3
		local lenght = toastContainer.Size.X.Scale/duration

		task.wait(0.5)

		misc.renderer.pushToRendering(function(delta, renderId)
			if running then
				toastBar.Size = toastBar.Size + UDim2.fromScale(lenght * delta, 0)

				if toastBar.Size.X.Scale >= 1 then
					misc.renderer.removeFromRendering(renderId)

					getgenv().arceus.garbage.toasts[newToast] = nil
					TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(newToast, TweenInfo.new(
						0.5, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.Out, 0, false, 0
						), { Position = UDim2.new(ogPosition.X.Scale, 0, newToast.Position.Y.Scale, newToast.Position.Y.Offset) }):Play()

					task.wait(0.5)
					newToast:Destroy()
				end
			end
		end)

		newToast.MouseButton1Down:Connect(function()
			running = false
		end)

		newToast.MouseButton1Up:Connect(function()
			running = true
		end)
	end

	getgenv().show_toast = show --newcclosure(show)
	testing_toast = show
end

--[[
		[ SIMPLE DECOMPILER ]
]]

do
	local function dictcounter(dict: table)
		local count = 0

		for k, v in pairs(dict) do
			count += 1
		end

		return count
	end

	local function arguments(count: number)
		local result = ""
		count = count or 0

		for i=1, count, 1 do
			result = result .. "arg" .. i .. (i<count and ", " or "")
		end

		return result
	end

	local function gettype(value: any)
		return typeof(value) .. (typeof(value) ~= type(value) and " (" .. type(value) .. ")" or "")
	end

	local function typescomment(key, value)
		return " \t-- " .. gettype(key) .. ", " .. gettype(value)
	end

	local formatvalue = nil
	local recursive = nil

	local function getgarbage(funct: funct, indent: string)
		local result = " "

		if not isStudio then
			local constants = ""
			local upvalues = ""

			pcall(function()
				for i, v in pairs(debug.getconstants(funct)) do
					local val, add = formatvalue(v, indent .. "\t", true, true)

					constants = constants .. "\n\t" .. indent .. formatvalue(i, indent .. "\t", true, true) .. ": " .. val .. add .. " -> " .. gettype(v)
				end
			end)

			pcall(function()
				for i, v in pairs(debug.getupvalues(funct)) do
					local val, add = formatvalue(v, indent .. "\t", true, true)

					upvalues = upvalues .. "\n\t" .. indent .. formatvalue(i, indent .. "\t", true, true) .. ": " .. val .. add .. " -> " .. gettype(v)
				end
			end)

			if constants ~= "" then
				result = result .. "\n" .. indent .. "\t-- constants" .. constants .. "\n"
			end

			if upvalues ~= "" then
				result = result .. "\n" .. indent .. "\t-- upvalues" .. upvalues .. "\n"
			end
		end

		return result
	end

	formatvalue = function(value: any, indent: string, commented: boolean, recurs: boolean)
		local result, atEnd = "", ""

		if typeof(value) == "string" then
			result = result .. "\"" .. value .. "\""
		elseif typeof(value) == "Instance" then
			result = result .. value:GetFullName():gsub("Workspace", "workspace")
		elseif typeof(value) == "function" then
			local line, name, args, variadic, address = debug.info(value, "lnaf")
			local garbage = getgarbage(value, indent)

			local comment = " \t-- " .. name .. " [" .. tostring(address):gsub("function: ", "") .. "]:" .. line
			if garbage == " " then
				atEnd = comment
				comment = ""
			elseif not commented then
				garbage = "\n" .. indent .. "--[[" .. garbage .. indent .. "]]\n" .. indent
			else
				garbage = garbage .. indent
			end

			result = result .. "function(" .. arguments(args) .. (variadic and (args > 0 and ", ..." or "...") or "") .. ")" .. comment .. garbage .. "end"
		elseif recurs and typeof(value) == "table" then
			recursive(value, indent .. "\t", recurs)
		else
			result = result .. tostring(value)
		end

		return result, atEnd
	end

	recursive = function(values: table, indent: string, dumpingRecurs: string)
		local result = ""
		local counter = 0
		local count = dictcounter(values)

		for key, value in pairs(values) do
			result = result .. "\n" .. indent .. "[" .. formatvalue(key, indent, false, dumpingRecurs) .. "] = "

			counter += 1
			local atEnd = ""

			if typeof(value) == "table" then
				result = result .. "{" .. typescomment(key, value) .. recursive(value, indent .. "\t") .. "\n" .. indent .. "}"
				atEnd = counter < count and "\n" or ""
			else
				local formatted, add = formatvalue(value, indent, false, dumpingRecurs)

				result = result .. formatted
				atEnd = add .. typescomment(key, value) .. ((typeof(value) == "function" and counter < count) and "\n" or "")
			end

			result = result .. (counter < count and "," or " ")
			result = result .. atEnd
		end

		return result
	end

	local decompile = function(target: ModuleScript)
		local result = "-- Arceus X simple decompiler failed to decompile." -- "-- Arceus X simple decompiler currently supports ModuleScripts only!"
		local completed = "-- Decompiled with Arceus X simple decompiler."
		local unsupported = "-- Arceus X simple decompiler supports LocalScripts, ModuleScripts, Functions & Tables only!"

		local function dec_function(funct)
			local suc, err = pcall(function()
				local name = debug.info(funct, "n")
				local tab = name == "" and {funct} or {[name] = funct}

				result = completed .. "\n\n" .. recursive(tab, "")
			end)

			if not suc and isStudio then
				error(err)
			end
		end

		if target then
			local isObject = typeof(target) == "Instance"

			if (isObject and target:IsA("ModuleScript")) or typeof(target) == "table" then
				completed = completed .. "\n-- Decompiling: " .. (typeof(target) == "Instance" and target:GetFullName() .. " -> " or "") .. gettype(target)

				local success, module = pcall(function()
					return typeof(target) == "table" and target or require(target)
				end)

				if success then
					local suc, err = pcall(function()
						result = completed .. "\n\nmodule = {" .. recursive(module, "\t") .. "\n}\n\nreturn module"	
					end)

					if not suc and isStudio then
						error(err)
					end
				end
			elseif isObject and target:IsA("LocalScript") then
				completed = completed .. (typeof(target) == "Instance" and "\n-- Decompiling: " .. target:GetFullName() .. " -> " .. gettype(target) or "")

				for _, funct in pairs(getgc()) do
					if typeof(funct) == "function" and getfenv(funct).script and getfenv(funct).script == target then
						dec_function(funct)
					end
				end
			elseif typeof(target) == "function" then
				dec_function(target)
			else
				result = unsupported .. "\n-- Trying to dump: " .. target:GetFullName() .. " -> " .. gettype(target)
			end
		else
			result = unsupported .. "\n-- Trying to dump value: " .. target .. " -> " .. gettype(target)
		end

		return result
	end

	getgenv().decompile = newcclosure(decompile)
	testing_decompiler = decompile
end

local showtoast = clonefunction(show_toast) or testing_toast -- Custom toast
getgenv().arceus = {
	show_toast = showtoast, -- Custom toast
	garbage = {}
}

--[[
		[ MISC FUNCTIONS ]
]]

--[[
local function randClass(object, len)
	setreadonly(object, false)
	sethiddenproperty(object, "ClassName", randString(len))
	setreadonly(object, true)
end
]]

local function closeGui()
	misc.renderer.stopRenddering()
	Main.Main:Destroy()
	script:Destroy()
end

local function deepCopy(data)
	local Copy = {}
	for k,v in pairs(data) do
		Copy[k] = typeof(v) == "table" and deepCopy(v) or v
	end

	return Copy
end

if not isStudio then
	--randClass(Main.Main)
end

misc = {
	url = {
		data = {
			loaded = false
		},

		open = function(url: string, noConfirm: boolean)
			if not misc.url.data.loaded then
				misc.url.data.loaded = true

				local popup = popups.create(popups.data.types.YesNo, "openurl")
				popup.OnResponse.Event:Connect(function(response, ...)
					local args = {...}

					if response and args[1] then --and openurl then
						--openurl(args[1])
						misc.clipboard.set(args[1])
						return
					end

					rconsole.warn("This exploit does not support openurl function!")
				end)
			end

			if noConfirm or not configs.getSetting("ConfirmationPopup") then
				--if openurl then
				--openurl(url)
				misc.clipboard.set(url)
				--end
			else
				local popup = popups.get("openurl")
				popup.Show("Opening link", "Do you want to open your browser?", url)
			end
		end,
	},

	clipboard = {
		set = function(str: string)
			str = tostring(str) or "Not a String"

			if setclipboard then
				setclipboard(str)
				misc.toast.short("Info", "Copied to clipboard!")
				return true
			end

			if toclipboard then
				toclipboard(str)
				misc.toast.short("Info", "Copied to clipboard!")
				return true
			end

			if isStudio then
				misc.toast.short("Info", "Copied to clipboard!")
			end

			rconsole.warn("This exploit does not support clipboard functions!")
			return false
		end,

		get = function()
			if getclipboard then
				return getclipboard() or ""
			end

			rconsole.warn("This exploit does not support clipboard functions!")
			return "Unable to get the clipboard!"
		end,
	},

	math = {
		lerp = function(a, b, t)
			return a + (b - a) * t
		end,

		outExpo = function(t)
			if t == 1 then
				return 1
			end

			return 1 - math.pow(2, -10 * t)
		end,

		currency = function(n: number)
			local units = {"k", "Mln", "Bil", "Tr", "Qa", "Qu"}

			for i=#units, 1, -1 do
				local limit = 10^(i*3)
				if n >= limit then
					if n < 10*limit then
						return string.format("%.2f%s", n/limit, units[i])
					elseif n < 100*limit then
						return string.format("%.1f%s", n/limit, units[i])
					else
						return string.format("%.0f%s", n/limit, units[i])
					end
				end
			end

			return tostring(n)
		end,

		countDict = function(dict: table)
			local c = 0
			for _, __ in pairs(dict) do
				c += 1
			end

			return c
		end
	},

	toast = {
		data = {
			send_toast = function(text: string, isLong: boolean, title: string)
				if showtoast then
					showtoast(text, isLong, title)
					return true
				end

				if isStudio then
					print(isLong and "LONG" or "SHORT", "POPUP:", text)
				end

				return false
			end
		},

		short = function(title: string, text: string)
			return misc.toast.data.send_toast(text, false, title)
		end,

		long = function(title: string, text: string)
			return misc.toast.data.send_toast(text, true, title)
		end
	},

	datetime = {
		secondsToHM = function(seconds: number)
			local Minutes = (seconds - seconds%60)/60
			seconds = seconds - Minutes*60
			local Hours = (Minutes - Minutes%60)/60
			Minutes = Minutes - Hours*60

			return string.format("%02i", Hours).."h ".. string.format("%02i", Minutes).."m"
		end,

		dateToDAgoHM = function(unix: number)
			local date = DateTime.fromUnixTimestamp(unix):ToLocalTime()
			return misc.datetime.dateToDAgo(unix) .. ", " .. string.format("%02i", date.Hour) ..":".. string.format("%02i", date.Minute), date.Day
		end,

		dateToDAgo = function(unix: number)
			local date = DateTime.fromUnixTimestamp(unix):ToLocalTime()
			local current = DateTime.now():ToLocalTime()

			local daysAgo = ""
			if date.Day < current.Day -1 then
				daysAgo = (current.Day - date.Day) .. " Days ago"
			else
				daysAgo = date.Day == current.Day and "Today" or "Yesterday"
			end

			return daysAgo
		end,

		secondsToDate = function(unix: number)
			local date = DateTime.fromUnixTimestamp(unix):ToLocalTime()

			local timeStamp = string.format("%02d", date.Day)
			timeStamp = timeStamp .. "/" .. string.format("%02d", date.Month)
			timeStamp = timeStamp .. "/" .. date.Year

			return timeStamp
		end,

		isoToUnix = function(iso: string)
			return DateTime.fromIsoDate(iso).UnixTimestamp
		end
	},

	crypt = {
		base64 = {
			encode = base64_encode or function(data: string)
				local b = 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/'
				return ((data:gsub('.', function(x) 
					local r,b='',x:byte()
					for i=8,1,-1 do r=r..(b%2^i-b%2^(i-1)>0 and '1' or '0') end
					return r;
				end)..'0000'):gsub('%d%d%d?%d?%d?%d?', function(x)
					if (#x < 6) then return '' end
					local c=0
					for i=1,6 do c=c+(x:sub(i,i)=='1' and 2^(6-i) or 0) end
					return b:sub(c+1,c+1)
				end)..({ '', '==', '=' })[#data%3+1])
			end,

			decode = base64_decode or function(data: string)
				local b = 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/'
				data = string.gsub(data, '[^'..b..'=]', '')
				return (data:gsub('.', function(x)
					if (x == '=') then return '' end
					local r,f='',(b:find(x)-1)
					for i=6,1,-1 do r=r..(f%2^i-f%2^(i-1)>0 and '1' or '0') end
					return r;
				end):gsub('%d%d%d?%d?%d?%d?%d?%d?', function(x)
					if (#x ~= 8) then return '' end
					local c=0
					for i=1,8 do c=c+(x:sub(i,i)=='1' and 2^(8-i) or 0) end
					return string.char(c)
				end))
			end
		},

		encryptDecrypt = function(data: string, key: string)
			local output = {}

			for i = 1, #data do
				local charValue = string.byte(data, i)
				local keyValue = string.byte(key, (i - 1) % 3 + 1)
				table.insert(output, string.char(bit32.bxor(charValue, keyValue)))
			end

			return table.concat(output)
		end
	},

	renderer = {
		data = {
			removedFromRendering = Instance.new("BindableEvent"),
			connection = nil,
			id_counter = 0,
			to_remove = {},
			functions = {},
			paused = {}
		},

		pauseFromRendering = function(id: number)
			misc.renderer.data.paused[id] = true
		end,

		resumeFromRendering = function(id: number)
			misc.renderer.data.paused[id] = nil
		end,

		removeFromRendering = function(id: number)		
			if misc.renderer.data.functions[id] then			
				misc.renderer.data.to_remove[id] = true
			end
		end,

		pushToRendering = function(funct)
			misc.renderer.data.id_counter += 1
			local new_id = "r" .. misc.renderer.data.id_counter

			misc.renderer.data.functions[new_id] = funct

			return new_id
		end,

		startRendering = function()
			if misc.renderer.data.connection then
				rconsole.warn("Rendered already connected!")
				return
			end

			misc.renderer.data.connection = RUN_SERVICE.RenderStepped:Connect(function(delta)
				pcall(function()
					for id, v in pairs(misc.renderer.data.functions) do
						if not misc.renderer.data.paused[id] then
							v(delta, id)
						end
					end

					local removed = false
					for id, v in pairs(misc.renderer.data.to_remove) do
						misc.renderer.data.functions[id] = nil
						misc.renderer.data.to_remove[id] = nil
						removed = true
					end

					if removed then
						misc.renderer.data.removedFromRendering:Fire()
					end
				end)
			end)
		end,

		stopRenddering = function()
			if misc.renderer.data.connection then
				misc.renderer.data.connection:Disconnect()
				misc.renderer.data.connection = nil
			end
		end,
	},

	animations = {
		data = {
			floating_icon = {
				state = false,
				elapsedTime = 0,
				floating_anim = nil,
				floating_running = false
			}
		},

		elementStatus = function(element: GuiObject, enabled: boolean)
			TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(element, TweenInfo.new(
				0.5, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, enabled and Enum.EasingDirection.In or Enum.EasingDirection.Out, 0, false, 0
				), { Transparency = enabled and 0 or 0.75 }):Play()
		end,

		floatingIcon = function(isOpening: boolean, yield: boolean, delta: number)
			local animationDuration = 0.5
			local spin_speed = 5

			misc.animations.data.floating_icon.state = isOpening
			misc.animations.data.floating_icon.elapsedTime = 0
			local subIcons = elements.data.floating_subicons

			local function calculatePosition(i)
				local t = misc.animations.data.floating_icon.elapsedTime / animationDuration
				local additional_angle = misc.math.lerp(0, 1, t)
				local angle = (i * (2 * math.pi / #subIcons)) + math.pi - (additional_angle * spin_speed % 360)

				local floatingIconRadius = Main.FloatingIcon.Size.X.Scale / 2
				local subIconRadius = Main.FloatingSub.Size.X.Scale / 2
				local distance = misc.math.lerp(0, floatingIconRadius + 3 * subIconRadius, t)

				local xScale = 0.5 + math.cos(angle) * distance
				local yScale = 0.5 + math.sin(angle) * distance
				return UDim2.new(xScale, 0, yScale, 0)
			end

			local function calculateClosingPosition(i)
				local t = 1 - (misc.animations.data.floating_icon.elapsedTime / animationDuration)
				local additional_angle = misc.math.lerp(0, 1, t)
				local angle = (i * (2 * math.pi / #subIcons)) + math.pi - (additional_angle * spin_speed % 360)

				local floatingIconRadius = Main.FloatingIcon.Size.X.Scale / 2
				local subIconRadius = Main.FloatingSub.Size.X.Scale / 2
				local distance = misc.math.lerp(0, floatingIconRadius + 3 * subIconRadius, t)

				local xScale = 0.5 + math.cos(angle) * distance
				local yScale = 0.5 + math.sin(angle) * distance
				return UDim2.new(xScale, 0, yScale, 0)
			end

			misc.animations.data.floating_icon.floating_running = true
			if isOpening then
				for _, subIcon in ipairs(subIcons) do
					subIcon.Visible = true
				end
			end

			if not misc.animations.data.floating_icon.floating_anim then
				misc.animations.data.floating_icon.floating_anim = misc.renderer.pushToRendering(function(delta)
					if misc.animations.data.floating_icon.floating_running then
						misc.animations.data.floating_icon.elapsedTime = misc.animations.data.floating_icon.elapsedTime + delta
						if misc.animations.data.floating_icon.elapsedTime > animationDuration then
							misc.animations.data.floating_icon.elapsedTime = animationDuration

							misc.animations.data.floating_icon.floating_running = false

							if not misc.animations.data.floating_icon.state then
								for _, subIcon in ipairs(subIcons) do
									subIcon.Visible = false
								end
							end
						end

						local t = misc.animations.data.floating_icon.elapsedTime / animationDuration
						local subIconTransparency, imageTransparency
						if misc.animations.data.floating_icon.state then
							subIconTransparency = misc.math.lerp(1, 0.5, misc.math.outExpo(t))
							imageTransparency = 1 - misc.math.outExpo(t)
						else
							subIconTransparency = misc.math.lerp(0.5, 1, misc.math.outExpo(t))
							imageTransparency = misc.math.outExpo(t)
						end

						for i, subIcon in ipairs(subIcons) do
							if misc.animations.data.floating_icon.state then
								subIcon.Position = calculatePosition(i)
							else
								subIcon.Position = calculateClosingPosition(i)
							end
							subIcon.BackgroundTransparency = subIconTransparency
							local label = subIcon:FindFirstChildWhichIsA("ImageLabel")
							if label then
								label.ImageTransparency = imageTransparency
							end
						end
					end
				end)
			end

			if yield then
				task.wait(animationDuration)
			end
		end,

		intro = function()
			Main.Intro.Visible = true
			Main.FloatingIcon.Visible = true

			TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(Main.Intro_SPDMLogo, TweenInfo.new(
				1.5, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.InOut, 0, true, 0
				), { ImageTransparency = 0 })

			task.wait(3)
			TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(Main.Intro_AXLogo, TweenInfo.new(
				1.5, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.InOut, 0, true, 0
				), { ImageTransparency = 0 })

			task.wait(3)
			TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(Main.Intro_ArceusXText, TweenInfo.new(
				1.5, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.InOut, 0, true, 0
				), { TextTransparency = 0 })

			task.wait(1)
			TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(Main.Intro, TweenInfo.new(
				0.5, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.Out, 0, false, 0
				), { Size = UDim2.fromScale(0, 0) })

			task.wait(0.6)
			Main.Intro.Visible = false

			--[[
			local originalPositions = {
				SideBar = Main.SideBar.Position,
				TopBar = Main.TopBar.Position,
				Body = Main.Body.Position
			}

			Main.SideBar.Position = UDim2.fromScale(-1, 0)
			Main.TopBar.Position = UDim2.fromScale(0, -1)
			Main.Body.Position = UDim2.fromScale(3, 3)

			Main.MainWindow.ClipsDescendants = false
			Main.MainWindow.BackgroundTransparency = 1
			Main.MainWindow.Visible = true
			
			task.wait(0.5)

			TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(Main.SideBar, TweenInfo.new(0.83), {Position = originalPositions.SideBar}):Play()
			TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(Main.TopBar, TweenInfo.new(0.83), {Position = originalPositions.TopBar}):Play()
			TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(Main.Body, TweenInfo.new(0.83), {Position = originalPositions.Body}):Play()
			TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(Main.MainWindow, TweenInfo.new(2.49), {BackgroundTransparency = 0.334}):Play()

			task.wait(0.9)

			local mainWindowPulseTween1 = TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(Main.MainWindow, TweenInfo.new(0.25), {Size = UDim2.new(.8, 0, .8, 0)})

			mainWindowPulseTween1:Play()
			mainWindowPulseTween1.Completed:Wait()
			TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(Main.MainWindow, TweenInfo.new(0.25), {Size = UDim2.new(.7, 0, .7, 0)}):Play()

			task.wait(0.6)
			Main.MainWindow.ClipsDescendants = true
			]]
		end,

		fadeImages = function(objects: table, fadeTime: tnumberime, transparency: number)
			for _, obj in ipairs(objects) do
				TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(obj, TweenInfo.new(
					fadeTime, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.Out, 0, false, 0
					), { ImageTransparency = transparency }):Play()
			end
		end,

		fadeObjects = function(objects: table, fadeTime: number, transparency: number)
			for _, obj in ipairs(objects) do
				TWEEN_SERVICE:Create(obj, TweenInfo.new(
					fadeTime, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.Out, 0, false, 0
					), { BackgroundTransparency = transparency }):Play()
			end
		end
	},

	tables = {
		value_changed = function(values: table, funct)
			local proxy = {}
			local meta = {}

			meta.__index = values
			meta.__newindex = function(t, k, v)
				funct(t, k, v)
			end

			return setmetatable(proxy, meta)
		end
	},

	socials = {
		instagram = function(noConf: boolean)
			misc.url.open("https://www.instagram.com/arceusxstatus", noConf)

		youtube = function(noConf: boolean)
			misc.url.open("https://www.youtube.com/SPDMTeam", noConf)

		tiktok = function(noConf: boolean)
			misc.url.open("https://www.tiktok.com/@arceusx_team", noConf)

		twitter = function(noConf: boolean)
			misc.url.open("https://twitter.com/ArceusX_Team", noConf)
		end,

		discord = function(noConf: boolean)
			misc.url.open("https://discord.com/invite/arceus", noConf)
		end,

		github = function(noConf: boolean)
			misc.url.open("https://github.com/SPDM-Team", noConf)
